A positive integer is given. Determine if the given number contains the digit "2".

Write a function called doesNumberContain2 that takes a number n as an argument and returns true if the number contains the number 2, and false otherwise. 
The use of string and array methods is prohibited. Use a do while loop in your solution.

Examples:

function doesNumberContain2 (1520) must return true;
the doesNumberContain2 (114876) function must return false;
doesNumberContain2 (22222) function must return true.


Solution:

function doesNumberContain2(n){
  let lastn;
  do {
     lastn = n % 10;
     n = (n - lastn) / 10;
     if (lastn === 2) {
     return true;
     }
  } while (n > 0);
  return false;
}
